{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/learning-disabilities/goals-outcome-measures/nice-quality-standards/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"b9a8bf11-ca0b-51a0-a965-d5058c0bceca","slug":"nice-quality-standards","fullItemName":"NICE quality standards","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 5bc617eb-b652-4589-8249-a8e200bd4669 --><h2>NICE quality standards</h2><!-- end field 5bc617eb-b652-4589-8249-a8e200bd4669 -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item afcff0c4-cb2e-4609-abbf-a8e200bd4669 --><!-- begin field 2af3c18e-9041-4587-8466-a8e200bd4669 --><p>NICE quality standards relating to people with learning disabilities which may be relevant to primary care include:</p><p><a href=\"http://www.nice.org.uk/guidance/qs101/chapter/quality-statement-1-comprehensive-health-assessment\" target=\"_top\" data-hyperlink-id=\"9507276e-64c3-43ed-96ec-a97300b64ff0\" data-original-url=\"http://publications.nice.org.uk/learning-disabilities-challenging-behaviour-qs101/quality-statement-1-comprehensive-health-assessment\">Statement 1</a> People with a learning disability have a comprehensive annual health assessment from their GP.</p><p><a href=\"http://www.nice.org.uk/guidance/qs101/chapter/quality-statement-2-initial-assessment-of-behaviour-that-challenges\" target=\"_top\" data-hyperlink-id=\"89521c91-c950-4713-8f21-a97300b6503f\" data-original-url=\"http://publications.nice.org.uk/learning-disabilities-challenging-behaviour-qs101/quality-statement-2-initial-assessment-of-behaviour-that-challenges\">Statement 2</a> People with a learning disability and behaviour that challenges have an initial assessment to identify possible triggers, environmental factors and function of the behaviour.</p><p><a href=\"http://www.nice.org.uk/guidance/qs101/chapter/quality-statement-6-use-of-medication\" target=\"_top\" data-hyperlink-id=\"189567d9-90f1-4536-b74c-a97300b6506e\" data-original-url=\"http://publications.nice.org.uk/learning-disabilities-challenging-behaviour-qs101/quality-statement-6-use-of-medication\">Statement 6</a> People with a learning disability and behaviour that challenges only receive antipsychotic medication as part of treatment that includes psychosocial interventions.</p><p><a href=\"http://www.nice.org.uk/guidance/qs101/chapter/quality-statement-7-review-of-medication\" target=\"_top\" data-hyperlink-id=\"707b1886-781d-40bb-888e-a97300b650ac\" data-original-url=\"http://publications.nice.org.uk/learning-disabilities-challenging-behaviour-qs101/quality-statement-7-review-of-medication\">Statement 7</a> People with a learning disability and behaviour that challenges have a multidisciplinary review of their antipsychotic medication 12 weeks after starting treatment and then at least every 6 months.</p><p><a href=\"http://www.nice.org.uk/guidance/qs101/chapter/quality-statement-8-family-and-carer-support\" target=\"_top\" data-hyperlink-id=\"603bb633-dbc2-4919-905c-a97300b650d9\" data-original-url=\"http://publications.nice.org.uk/learning-disabilities-challenging-behaviour-qs101/quality-statement-8-family-and-carer-support\">Statement 8</a> Parents or carers of children aged under 12 years with a learning disability and behaviour that challenges are offered a parent‑training programme.</p><p>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/learning-disabilities/references/\">NICE, 2015b</a>]</p><p><a href=\"https://www.nice.org.uk/guidance/qs142/chapter/quality-statement-1-annual-health-check#quality-statement-1-annual-health-check\" target=\"_top\" rel=\"internal\" data-chapter=\"quality-statement-1-annual-health-check\" data-hyperlink-id=\"040682ec-3b0b-43f7-8e96-a97300b65107\" data-original-url=\"#quality-statement-1-annual-health-check\">Statement 1</a> Young people and adults with learning disabilities have an annual health check that includes a review of mental health problems.</p><p><a href=\"https://www.nice.org.uk/guidance/qs142/chapter/quality-statement-2-assessment-by-a-professional-with-relevant-expertise#quality-statement-2-assessment-by-a-professional-with-relevant-expertise\" target=\"_top\" rel=\"internal\" data-chapter=\"quality-statement-2-assessment-by-a-professional-with-relevant-expertise\" data-hyperlink-id=\"566e2587-b7b7-4ab0-8ed1-a97300b65126\" data-original-url=\"#quality-statement-2-assessment-by-a-professional-with-relevant-expertise\">Statement 2</a> People with learning disabilities who need a mental health assessment are referred to a professional with expertise in mental health problems in people with learning disabilities.</p><p><a href=\"https://www.nice.org.uk/guidance/qs142/chapter/quality-statement-4-tailoring-psychological-interventions#quality-statement-4-tailoring-psychological-interventions\" target=\"_top\" rel=\"internal\" data-chapter=\"quality-statement-4-tailoring-psychological-interventions\" data-hyperlink-id=\"3ff278c6-635a-4ee2-b428-a97300b65143\" data-original-url=\"#quality-statement-4-tailoring-psychological-interventions\">Statement 4</a> People with learning and mental health problems who are receiving psychological interventions have them tailored to their preferences, level of understanding, and strengths and needs.</p><p><a href=\"https://www.nice.org.uk/guidance/qs142/chapter/quality-statement-5-annually-documenting-the-reasons-for-continuing-antipsychotic-drugs#quality-statement-5-annually-documenting-the-reasons-for-continuing-antipsychotic-drugs\" target=\"_top\" rel=\"internal\" data-chapter=\"quality-statement-5-annually-documenting-the-reasons-for-continuing-antipsychotic-drugs\" data-hyperlink-id=\"87239987-701d-4fc8-b98e-a97300b6527f\" data-original-url=\"#quality-statement-5-annually-documenting-the-reasons-for-continuing-antipsychotic-drugs\">Statement 5</a> People with learning disabilities who are taking antipsychotic drugs that are not reduced or stopped have annual documentation on reasons for continuing this prescription.</p><p>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/learning-disabilities/references/\">NICE, 2017</a>]</p><p><a href=\"https://www.nice.org.uk/guidance/qs194/chapter/Quality-statement-1-Supported-decision-making\" data-hyperlink-id=\"b49e210f-9646-4bbb-8f37-ac1700b60c8c\">Statement 1</a> People aged 16 and over who may lack capacity to make decisions are supported with decision making in a way that reﬂects their individual circumstances and meets their particular needs.</p><p><a href=\"https://www.nice.org.uk/guidance/qs194/chapter/Quality-statement-2-Advance-care-plans\" data-hyperlink-id=\"19175842-d0f8-4dfd-84c1-ac1700b60caf\">Statement 2</a> People aged 16 and over at risk of losing capacity to make decisions, and those with fluctuating capacity, are given the opportunity to discuss advance care planning at each health and social care review.</p><p><a href=\"https://www.nice.org.uk/guidance/qs194/chapter/Quality-statement-3-Assessment-of-capacity\" data-hyperlink-id=\"e521fa47-0840-49f9-8535-ac1700b60cca\">Statement 3</a> People aged 16 and over who are assessed as lacking capacity to make a particular decision at the time that decision needs to be made, have a clear record of the reasons why they lack capacity and the practicable steps taken to support them.</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><a href=\"https://www.nice.org.uk/guidance/qs194/chapter/Quality-statement-4-Best-interests-decision-making\" data-hyperlink-id=\"0d9a87ab-e326-448f-bd9c-ac1700b60cee\">Statement 4</a> People aged 16 and over who lack capacity to make a particular decision at the time that decision needs to be made have their wishes, feelings, values and beliefs accounted for in best interests decisions.</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"> </p><p>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/learning-disabilities/references/\">NICE, 2020</a>]</p><!-- end field 2af3c18e-9041-4587-8466-a8e200bd4669 --><!-- end item afcff0c4-cb2e-4609-abbf-a8e200bd4669 -->","topic":{"id":"81b6bf13-1851-5aca-a415-deb2664fff5b","topicId":"9cc09e0b-a51c-445a-a0f0-a8e200bd3e76","topicName":"Learning disabilities","slug":"learning-disabilities","lastRevised":"Last revised in August 2020","chapters":[{"id":"433a4d95-fb0e-597f-886b-7a5bba677e2e","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"e6952a3b-5351-51c3-b34d-3ce4fd90e136","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"cd675bbe-842b-5eac-9101-92f52a07ffd0","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"42e6170c-2ad4-5c42-98b5-66bb0f315b56","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"cdef379f-d2ef-5c80-9644-6e1cb6864f2a","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"f8ff91d6-3a99-5f81-ab3e-b522150de1f1","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"dbf4d83d-021c-5c6c-8be4-5637c384ed7b","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"73bb96cd-3d7f-50c7-8bd6-2c3f50a56d70","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"4e9fbda8-d558-51be-9f50-16e404570513","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemName":"Audit criteria"},{"id":"8a99509d-dcc3-52cf-be04-85ee2c4aad00","slug":"qof-indicators","fullItemName":"QOF indicators"},{"id":"88e8dc33-8096-57aa-accc-3ec205effbe3","slug":"qipp-options-for-local-implementation","fullItemName":"QIPP - Options for local implementation"},{"id":"b9a8bf11-ca0b-51a0-a965-d5058c0bceca","slug":"nice-quality-standards","fullItemName":"NICE quality standards"}]},{"id":"40e1752f-d69e-5ab7-9d4a-751e3289532f","fullItemName":"Background information","slug":"background-information","subChapters":[{"id":"f13e3735-ce06-52c4-a330-2ed80d3bd1db","slug":"definition","fullItemName":"Definition"},{"id":"e2c46c5d-8972-5934-9c2a-7e6a370aaf81","slug":"prevalence","fullItemName":"Prevalence"},{"id":"432f94cd-ae01-5de8-aedc-0b0ca066f01b","slug":"risk-factors","fullItemName":"Risk factors"},{"id":"6d615282-75db-51f0-a502-caab96337165","slug":"complications-prognosis","fullItemName":"Complications and prognosis"}]},{"id":"3e168af4-366c-5883-b8e2-f10a900203b9","fullItemName":"Diagnosis","slug":"diagnosis","subChapters":[{"id":"6f93bf68-ee6a-5cca-945c-edac36347b11","slug":"diagnosis","fullItemName":"Diagnosis"}]},{"id":"1023b7ee-da44-5608-93e7-0d0361e2bdbe","fullItemName":"Management","slug":"management","subChapters":[{"id":"63437873-b64a-5f3b-9349-73033c126cc9","slug":"suspected-learning-disability","fullItemName":"Scenario: Suspected learning disability"},{"id":"cde5b7a3-65e9-5519-8ba3-6f28c1edf1ee","slug":"confirmed-learning-disability","fullItemName":"Scenario: Confirmed learning disability"},{"id":"658ba274-21c6-574b-b7a8-81d968ca5702","slug":"behaviour-that-challenges-mental-health-problems","fullItemName":"Scenario: Behaviour that challenges and mental health problems"}]},{"id":"7c2b476c-d197-54fe-90d2-7ed4ec49e103","fullItemName":"Supporting evidence","slug":"supporting-evidence","subChapters":[]},{"id":"5d7ee2c8-572a-5444-bbdc-b66f157b7c7d","fullItemName":"How this topic was developed","slug":"how-this-topic-was-developed","subChapters":[{"id":"4fa0c0b5-be1f-57f2-958e-597ba3d36eba","slug":"search-strategy","fullItemName":"Search strategy"},{"id":"257eba34-aad1-5a9b-92b8-65f0ed224fb3","slug":"stakeholder-engagement","fullItemName":"Stakeholder engagement"},{"id":"99791e8d-d65b-573e-8907-07ff851cb6a2","slug":"evidence-exclusion-criteria","fullItemName":"Evidence exclusion criteria"},{"id":"c31529b2-263b-541e-833e-2926c92f7847","slug":"organizational-behavioural-financial-barriers","fullItemName":"Organizational, behavioural and financial barriers"},{"id":"fa2e8dd7-1128-5824-b391-29a2ade6d4f5","slug":"declarations-of-interest","fullItemName":"Declarations of interest"}]},{"id":"e3a9941b-b74a-59c0-8bf5-66ce8ec74f4f","fullItemName":"References","slug":"references","subChapters":[]}]},"parentChapter":{"id":"f8ff91d6-3a99-5f81-ab3e-b